'''Ammonium adipate''' is a [[Compound (chemistry)|compound]] with formula (NH<sub>4</sub>)<sub>2</sub>(C<sub>4</sub>H<sub>8</sub>(COO)<sub>2</sub>). It is the [[ammonium]] salt of [[adipic acid]].  It is used as a [[food additive]] and has the [[E number]] E359.


