The [[Papua conflict|unification]] (or re-unification) of [[Papua New Guinea]] (or East Papua), an [[Sovereign state|independent state]], and [[Republic of West Papua|West Papua]] (or Western New Guinea), a territory of [[Indonesia]], both parts of the [[New Guinea]] island, has been raised since the second half of the 20th century.

West Papuans have conducted [[Papua conflict|various protests]] and ceremonies raising [[Morning Star flag|their flag]] for independence or federation with [[Papua New Guinea]]<ref name="fas">{{cite web|url=http://www.fas.org/irp/world/para/papua.htm|title=Free Papua Movement|first=John|last=Pike|date=17 April 2009|accessdate=20 April 2011|publisher=[[Federation of American Scientists]]}}</ref>

