[[File:Coat of arms of Poland (1955-1980).svg|thumb|right|200px|PRL c.o.a (1955-1980)]] '''Polska Ludowa''' ({{IPA-pl|ˈpɔlska luˈdɔva|lang}}, {{lit.}} ''People's Poland'') was a semi-official reference to the [[Polish People's Republic|Polish state under Communism]]. The term was intended to imply the power of the [[working people]] in the state.<ref>[http://portalwiedzy.onet.pl/94908,,,,polska_ludowa,haslo.html "Polska Ludowa"]</ref> It was a colloquial reference, including official speeches, but was also sometimes used in official documents.
The official names of the state were: *[[Rzeczpospolita]] Polska (1944-1952) (literally "Polish Commonwealth") *Polska Rzeczpospolita Ludowa (1952-1989), [[Polish People's Republic]]
